### Section VIII: Wave-Particle Duality & The Double-Slit Sieve

The wave-particle paradox of classical quantum mechanics is an artifact of treating empty space as an absolute void and particles as zero-dimensional abstract points. By replacing the abstract probability wavefunction with a physical, dual-zone loop structure interacting with an underlying photon-scale medium, the double-slit experiment resolves as a deterministic fluid-mechanical sorting machine.

